00:14:59,608 --> 00:15:01,610
Eh, look, let's talk to him
about this record.

254
00:15:01,694 --> 00:15:03,779
Hey, no, no, we're gonna
let Marlene handle that.

255
00:15:03,863 --> 00:15:05,781
You get Oberon
to call you a cab, all right.

256
00:15:05,865 --> 00:15:07,408
Great set, Ray.

257
00:15:08,534 --> 00:15:09,743
Goss!

258
00:15:09,785 --> 00:15:11,912
Hey, daddy-o, want a smoke?

259
00:15:12,454 --> 00:15:14,456
I got some gage, fresh off the boat.

260
00:15:14,498 --> 00:15:15,958
It's clean and seedless.

261
00:15:16,041 --> 00:15:17,793
So that's how it is, huh?

262
00:15:18,002 --> 00:15:20,796
You keep me high
while they talk the business?

263
00:15:20,963 --> 00:15:22,673
I ain't the one playing you, man.

264
00:15:25,801 --> 00:15:27,094
Oberon, listen ...

265
00:15:27,386 --> 00:15:30,764
You know, Marlene and Gossie are the 
ones running the game on you, Ray.

266
00:15:30,806 --> 00:15:31,891
What?

267
00:15:31,974 --> 00:15:34,477
They sliced up the pie
the first night you played.

268
00:15:34,560 --> 00:15:36,270
35 percent off the top.

269
00:15:36,353 --> 00:15:38,397
Plus Gossie's
double scale as leader.

270
00:15:38,814 --> 00:15:40,107
Leader?
If anybody's leading the band,

271
00:15:40,149 --> 00:15:42,359
I'm the one that's the leader.

272
00:15:42,651 --> 00:15:44,195
Forget the bo' humps.
You know what?

273
00:15:44,278 --> 00:15:45,613
I ... I'm ... I'm gonna go
my own way.

274
00:15:45,696 --> 00:15:47,573
Who's gonna book your gigs?

275
00:15:47,698 --> 00:15:49,617
Marlene's got you locked up.

276
00:15:49,658 --> 00:15:52,453
And she ain't gonna give up
her golden goose.

277
00:15:52,578 --> 00:15:55,289
♪ Straighten up and fly right ♪

278
00:15:55,331 --> 00:15:57,875
♪ Cool down, papa,
don't you blow your top ♪

279
00:15:57,958 --> 00:16:00,127
Hey, Ray Robinson,
you are fantastic.

280
00:16:01,045 --> 00:16:03,339
There you go. Give me some skin.

281
00:16:04,965 --> 00:16:06,050
What's that?

282
00:16:06,133 --> 00:16:07,301
Jack's card.

283
00:16:07,384 --> 00:16:09,470
I got his number at the hotel.

284
00:16:15,309 --> 00:16:17,269
Come on, Q.
It's not that complicated.

285
00:16:17,353 --> 00:16:18,646
Now let's just play it again.

286
00:16:18,729 --> 00:16:20,564
That's a B flat, C 7, scale it up,

287
00:16:20,648 --> 00:16:22,566
and triple it off the back end.

288
00:16:24,860 --> 00:16:27,029
Yeah, nigger! Yeah, that's it.

289
00:16:28,572 --> 00:16:31,659
Ray, what did I tell you
about cookin' in the dark?

290
00:16:31,700 --> 00:16:33,369
Are you tryin'
to burn the house down?

291
00:16:33,452 --> 00:16:35,996
Think about it, Marlene. Uh ... uh, 
what do I need the light for?

292
00:16:36,038 --> 00:16:37,832
Well, you don't need
to be cookin' anyway.

293
00:16:37,873 --> 00:16:39,458
We brought you
takeout from Oscar's.

294
00:16:39,542 --> 00:16:40,584
Well, get your money back.

295
00:16:40,668 --> 00:16:42,002
I got fried chicken right here.

296
00:16:42,086 --> 00:16:43,379
Come on, Seven-oh, try this.

297
00:16:43,462 --> 00:16:44,964
Yeah! About time.

298
00:16:46,799 --> 00:16:48,634
Hey, that's home-cooked,
right there.

299
00:16:48,717 --> 00:16:49,844
Mmm, no, thank you.

300
00:16:49,927 --> 00:16:51,345
This chicken is the mostest, huh.

301
00:16:51,387 --> 00:16:53,681
Just needs a little hot sauce
and it'll be perfect.

302
00:16:53,722 --> 00:16:55,766
Yeah. So, what did
Jack Lauderdale have to say?

303
00:16:55,850 --> 00:16:57,434
Oh, I clocked him
comin' out the gate.

304
00:16:57,518 --> 00:16:58,769
He's a two-bit hustler.

305
00:16:58,853 --> 00:17:00,020
Oh, I see.

306
00:17:00,062 --> 00:17:02,606
Yeah, turns out the only hit
that Swing Time ever had ...

307
00:17:02,690 --> 00:17:04,859
was Open the Door, Richard,
which was a joke record.

308
00:17:04,942 --> 00:17:06,819
Uh ... uh ... uh, what about him
recordin' me?

309
00:17:06,902 --> 00:17:09,238
Oh, he'll record you,
if we pay the freight.

310
00:17:09,405 --> 00:17:11,031
Scratch a liar, find a thief.

311
00:17:12,158 --> 00:17:13,659
What's that supposed to mean?

312
00:17:13,742 --> 00:17:14,952
This.

313
00:17:15,703 --> 00:17:17,580
You see I saw
Jack Lauderdale tonight,

314
00:17:17,663 --> 00:17:19,707
and he gave me a $500
advance on my record.

315
00:17:19,748 --> 00:17:22,042
He also said he'll put me
on the road with Lowell Fulson ...

316
00:17:22,084 --> 00:17:23,627
and pay me three times
what you pay.

317
00:17:23,711 --> 00:17:24,837
Now, that's a lie!

318
00:17:24,920 --> 00:17:28,340
Hey, no way he's not gonna put some 
blind man on the road. Think about it.

319
00:17:28,424 --> 00:17:30,342
I mean, you ... you need
watchin' out for.

320
00:17:30,426 --> 00:17:32,636
And he ain't got the time to 
look after you the way I do.

321
00:17:32,720 --> 00:17:35,139
Is that what you've been doing, 
Gossie? Watchin' out for me?

322
00:17:35,222 --> 00:17:37,057
Is that why you get
paid double what I do?

323
00:17:38,601 --> 00:17:39,768
Who told you that?

324
00:17:39,852 --> 00:17:40,895
It's true, ain't it?

325
00:17:40,978 --> 00:17:42,980
You two have been
gaming me since I got here.

326
00:17:43,063 --> 00:17:45,024
Ray, baby, listen ...
I ain't listening to you!

327
00:17:45,107 --> 00:17:47,485
Ray, I've ... I've been meaning 
to talk to you about that.

328
00:17:47,568 --> 00:17:49,612
Then why aren't you talkin'?

329
00:17:51,989 --> 00:17:54,241
Um, look, Ray, Ray,
let's not do nothin' stupid.

330
00:17:54,283 --> 00:17:56,076
I might be blind,
but I ain't stupid!

331
00:17:56,118 --> 00:17:57,828
Q., get my bag from upstairs.

332
00:17:57,912 --> 00:17:59,038
- What?
- Get it!

333
00:17:59,121 --> 00:18:00,581
- Wha ... right now?
- Now.

334
00:18:00,664 --> 00:18:02,917
Ray, man, we done been
through a whole lot.

335
00:18:02,958 --> 00:18:05,711
Ray, now wait a minute.
I can explain everything.

336
00:18:06,003 --> 00:18:07,713
Think about what you're doing.

337
00:18:07,797 --> 00:18:09,632
Ray, Ray, now you're makin'
a big mistake.

338
00:18:09,715 --> 00:18:11,717
That clown is spoutin'
promises that he can't keep.

339
00:18:11,801 --> 00:18:13,552
You'd be a fool to follow him.

340
00:18:13,636 --> 00:18:14,929
Ray, Ray, we'll make a new deal!

341
00:18:15,012 --> 00:18:16,138
Whatever makes you happy!

342
00:18:16,222 --> 00:18:18,140
The deal is
you can lay the pipe now.

343
00:18:18,224 --> 00:18:21,644
You'll break your neck going down 
these stairs by yourself. Hang on.

344
00:18:22,102 --> 00:18:23,145
Oh, man.

345
00:18:23,229 --> 00:18:26,982
Ray, I ain't never seen you do 
nothing like that, man. Never.

346
00:18:27,066 --> 00:18:28,776
That ain't nothing, Seven-oh.

347
00:18:41,747 --> 00:18:43,582
Stop cheating, Ray.

348
00:18:44,416 --> 00:18:47,044
George, you can't catch me.
Come on.

349
00:18:47,128 --> 00:18:48,462
Aretha!

350
00:18:49,171 --> 00:18:50,464
Come on, George.

351
00:18:50,548 --> 00:18:53,050
Aretha Robinson,
have you lost your mind?

352
00:18:53,134 --> 00:18:56,428
Eula, you promised to split every 
wash basket with me, fair and square!

353
00:18:56,512 --> 00:18:57,596
And I did!

354
00:18:57,680 --> 00:18:58,764
Hell, you did!

355
00:18:58,848 --> 00:19:00,933
You charge white folks
one thing and pay me another.

356
00:19:01,016 --> 00:19:02,434
Now who's gonna wash these?

357
00:19:02,518 --> 00:19:03,978
You can. Now pay me my money!

358
00:19:07,565 --> 00:19:09,567
Okay, I'm a-giving you
your two little dollars.

359
00:19:09,650 --> 00:19:11,777
But don't you be expectin'
no more work out of me!

360
00:19:11,861 --> 00:19:13,279
I got all I need out of you.

361
00:19:13,404 --> 00:19:14,864
Ray and George, come on!

362
00:19:14,905 --> 00:19:16,532
That's right. 
Get out of my yard ...

363
00:19:16,615 --> 00:19:18,367
and don't y'all never come back!

364
00:19:21,287 --> 00:19:24,039
Y'all got to learn
to read and write real good,

365
00:19:24,123 --> 00:19:26,876
so you never have to work
for people like that.

366
00:19:26,959 --> 00:19:28,669
Scratch a liar, find a thief.

367
00:19:28,711 --> 00:19:29,712
Understand?

368
00:19:29,753 --> 00:19:30,921
Yes, Mama.

369
00:19:43,893 --> 00:19:46,520
Smell that, Ray.
Smell the success.

370
00:19:46,812 --> 00:19:48,230
We're in LA, man,

371
00:19:48,272 --> 00:19:50,566
the place where the Negro
comes to spread his wings.

372
00:19:50,649 --> 00:19:53,068
You ... you know, man, I know
my ears ain't deceivin' me.

373
00:19:53,110 --> 00:19:54,153
Is that Art Tatum?

374
00:19:54,236 --> 00:19:55,863
It sure is, baby.
You want to meet him?

375
00:19:55,946 --> 00:19:58,616
I ... I can't meet him.
A-Art Tatum is the most.

376
00:20:03,871 --> 00:20:08,334
So, Ray, we got to talk about 
your name, man: Robinson.

377
00:20:08,417 --> 00:20:11,295
Sugar Ray got the Robinson
franchise all sewed up.

378
00:20:11,378 --> 00:20:15,049
So I'm thinkin' we go with
your middle name, Charles.

379
00:20:15,591 --> 00:20:16,967
As in, Ray Charles.

380
00:20:17,051 --> 00:20:18,761
I don't care
what you call me, man,

381
00:20:18,844 --> 00:20:20,638
just as long as my name's
on the record.

382
00:20:20,721 --> 00:20:22,097
But we're gonna toast to that.

383
00:20:22,181 --> 00:20:23,474
Hey, what's the haps, Jack?

384
00:20:23,557 --> 00:20:25,184
Oh, my goodness.
Give me some skin.

385
00:20:25,267 --> 00:20:27,311
What's up, baby?
How you doin'?

386
00:20:27,394 --> 00:20:30,981
Lowell Fulson, meet your new
piano player: Ray Charles.

387
00:20:31,065 --> 00:20:33,609
Ray Charles, the blind sensation.

388
00:20:33,692 --> 00:20:37,488
Ow! Damn! I'm gonna use that
on the album cover.

389
00:20:37,571 --> 00:20:38,989
He's really the sensation.

390
00:20:39,073 --> 00:20:40,908
I ... I love your music,
Mr. Fulson.

391
00:20:40,950 --> 00:20:42,368
Uh, the man's got taste.

392
00:20:42,451 --> 00:20:44,745
Hey, and the man ain't
been on the road ...

393
00:20:44,787 --> 00:20:47,039
with a band before,
so now you take care of him.

394
00:20:47,122 --> 00:20:48,457
Like my own brother.

395
00:20:52,044 --> 00:20:53,295
Ray.

396
00:20:54,171 --> 00:20:55,297
I'm gonna be right back.

397
00:20:55,381 --> 00:20:56,423
All right.

398
00:20:56,966 --> 00:20:59,593
Yeah, you got the one
on the left.

399
00:20:59,635 --> 00:21:01,428
Look here,
let me do the talking.

400
00:21:30,249 --> 00:21:31,750
Don't go inside that place.

401
00:21:31,834 --> 00:21:33,294
You know what Mama said.

402
00:21:33,335 --> 00:21:35,838
Go home
and don't tell Mama nothin'.

403
00:21:36,338 --> 00:21:37,715
Go, George.

404
00:21:42,178 --> 00:21:44,013
George, get out of here!

405
00:22:09,788 --> 00:22:12,625
Hey, boy, who let you in?

406
00:22:12,875 --> 00:22:15,002
You must be Aretha's son, huh?

407
00:22:15,044 --> 00:22:17,296
Yes, sir. Ray Charles Robinson.

408
00:22:17,755 --> 00:22:20,508
I've been seeing you
sneakin' around here.

409
00:22:20,841 --> 00:22:22,510
You like the piano, huh?

410
00:22:23,093 --> 00:22:25,137
Come on, you want
to learn how to play?

411
00:22:25,221 --> 00:22:26,514
Come on over here.

412
00:22:26,555 --> 00:22:28,307
Let me show you how to play.
Come on.

413
00:22:28,390 --> 00:22:30,601
I'm gonna teach you how to play.

414
00:22:30,684 --> 00:22:33,604
What we'll do, I'm gonna teach
you three notes, right?

415
00:22:33,687 --> 00:22:35,773
This is the first note,
right here.

416
00:22:37,358 --> 00:22:38,442
Play that.

417
00:22:39,735 --> 00:22:41,946
And here's the second note,
right here.

418
00:22:43,113 --> 00:22:44,365
Play that.

419
00:22:46,075 --> 00:22:47,701
Here's the third note.

420
00:22:50,746 --> 00:22:52,039
Now, here's the way it goes.

421
00:22:52,122 --> 00:22:53,707
Listen. Listen closely, now.

422
00:22:57,461 --> 00:22:58,796
Play that.

423
00:23:00,381 --> 00:23:01,715
Good!

424
00:23:02,883 --> 00:23:04,635
Try the other notes.

425
00:23:13,477 --> 00:23:14,937
Every club we hit,

426
00:23:15,020 --> 00:23:17,481
it's your responsibility
to rehearse the band.

427
00:23:17,606 --> 00:23:19,608
These are some lazy-ass bastards,

428
00:23:19,692 --> 00:23:21,986
so you gotta make sure
that they don't slough off.

429
00:23:22,403 --> 00:23:24,530
You gotta be ready
and dressed to open the show.

430
00:23:24,613 --> 00:23:26,949
Now, Lowell likes to take
a nap before he goes on.

431
00:23:27,032 --> 00:23:30,077
You just do your thing
until he feels like comin' out.

432
00:23:30,161 --> 00:23:33,080
And when Lowell's playin',
you keep the band sharp.

433
00:23:33,122 --> 00:23:34,123
Uh ... uh, just one thing.

434
00:23:34,206 --> 00:23:35,124
What?

435
00:23:35,207 --> 00:23:37,334
Did Jack tell you that
I have to be paid in singles?

436
00:23:38,463 --> 00:23:40,847
You just do your job,
you're gonna get your money.

437
00:23:41,589 --> 00:23:43,257
♪ Baby, come on, down ♪

438
00:23:43,299 --> 00:23:46,469
♪ Your daddy's
in the heart of town ♪

439
00:23:50,222 --> 00:23:51,724
♪ Come on down ♪

440
00:23:51,807 --> 00:23:55,227
♪ Your daddy's in the heart of town ♪

441
00:24:01,484 --> 00:24:03,819
How'd you get the name
Fathead anyway?

442
00:24:03,903 --> 00:24:05,404
Why do they call me Fathead?

443
00:24:05,529 --> 00:24:07,072
Nah, you don't want to hear.

444
00:24:07,156 --> 00:24:09,116
But this is what
I really want to know.

445
00:24:09,200 --> 00:24:11,285
Do any of you
fine young ladies know ...

446
00:24:11,327 --> 00:24:13,704
where we can get a nice steak
this time of night?

447
00:24:13,787 --> 00:24:16,791
You mean something big,
thick, and juicy?

448
00:24:16,874 --> 00:24:18,667
Oh, yeah, that's just what I mean.

449
00:24:19,919 --> 00:24:22,171
Fathead, where you guys
headed, man?

450
00:24:22,755 --> 00:24:24,840
I ain't babysittin' no blind cat.

451
00:24:25,841 --> 00:24:27,259
Uh, I'm sorry, Ray,

452
00:24:27,343 --> 00:24:30,054
but, uh, the law says
there's only six to a cab.

453
00:24:30,137 --> 00:24:32,139
Come on, ladies,
let's get out of here.

454
00:25:28,904 --> 00:25:31,073
♪ Everyday ♪

455
00:25:36,245 --> 00:25:39,915
♪ Everyday I have the blues ♪

456
00:25:46,422 --> 00:25:49,758
♪ Everyday, everyday ♪

457
00:25:54,096 --> 00:25:56,390
Pay up, baby!
Yeah, that's all right.

458
00:25:56,432 --> 00:25:58,726
I been shootin' craps
since I was 12 years old.

459
00:25:58,767 --> 00:26:01,353
Don't never shoot craps
on a white woman's grave.

460
00:26:01,437 --> 00:26:02,396
Why not?

461
00:26:02,480 --> 00:26:03,564
It's bad luck.

462
00:26:03,606 --> 00:26:07,026
♪ You know bad luck
and trouble, people ♪

463
00:26:10,404 --> 00:26:13,073
♪ Well, you know I had my share ♪

464
00:26:19,371 --> 00:26:21,081
That's for being late to the bus.

465
00:26:21,123 --> 00:26:22,625
Wilbur, you a low-down piece ...

466
00:26:22,708 --> 00:26:24,168
You better move on.

467
00:26:29,632 --> 00:26:31,801
Ah, Mr. One-dollar Bill.

468
00:26:32,843 --> 00:26:36,514
$5, $10, $15, $20 ...

469
00:26:37,640 --> 00:26:40,267
Now, you like to start
counting that again?

470
00:26:41,477 --> 00:26:43,312
All right, damn you.

471
00:26:45,648 --> 00:26:47,817
$284, $285 ...

472
00:26:47,900 --> 00:26:50,736
Listen, man, I ain't
no damn seein'-eye dog.

473
00:26:50,820 --> 00:26:54,240
♪ You know ain't nobody worried
about me ♪

474
00:26:55,825 --> 00:27:00,496
♪ I don't see nobody, nobody cryin' ♪

475
00:27:07,503 --> 00:27:09,964
Fathead, open up. Open up.
I got to take a leak.

476
00:27:12,967 --> 00:27:15,761
Hey, what you doing, man?
Close the door, Fat!

477
00:27:16,011 --> 00:27:18,305
Say, Ray, we'll be in here
for a little while.

478
00:27:18,347 --> 00:27:21,142
Use the women's can,
down there on your right.

479
00:27:21,225 --> 00:27:22,768
I don't want to use
the women's can.

480
00:27:22,852 --> 00:27:23,894
This way, alright.

