2497
02:06:28,186 --> 02:06:29,270
It's awful big.

2498
02:06:29,354 --> 02:06:30,939
It sure is: 8,500 square feet.

2499
02:06:31,022 --> 02:06:32,816
Biggest house in the neighborhood.

2500
02:06:32,857 --> 02:06:34,651
So, does this meet
with your approval?

2501
02:06:34,693 --> 02:06:36,194
Man, this is a palace.

2502
02:06:36,277 --> 02:06:38,780
You think this is big? Wait 
until tomorrow when you see ...

2503
02:06:38,863 --> 02:06:41,157
30,000 square feet
of RPM Incorporated.

2504
02:06:41,199 --> 02:06:42,992
Yeah, headquarters!

2505
02:06:43,034 --> 02:06:45,412
This is it, Ray. 
Your brand-new recording studio.

2506
02:06:45,495 --> 02:06:47,122
Did you get everything I asked for?

2507
02:06:47,205 --> 02:06:48,456
Totally state-of-the-art.

2508
02:06:48,540 --> 02:06:52,502
Tom Dowd built an eight-track mixing 
console, two recorders, the works.

2509
02:06:52,544 --> 02:06:54,963
Now, this room is bigger
than most people's houses.

2510
02:06:55,046 --> 02:06:57,465
- Got your own private bathroom
to your left. - Good.

2511
02:06:57,549 --> 02:06:59,801
Right behind you
is my adjoining office.

2512
02:06:59,884 --> 02:07:02,220
And step over to your 
private bar to your left.

2513
02:07:02,303 --> 02:07:04,222
Got a bottle of Bols
right in the center.

2514
02:07:04,264 --> 02:07:05,682
You know me pretty good.

2515
02:07:05,724 --> 02:07:08,143
If you run out, shout,
I'm right next door.

2516
02:07:08,476 --> 02:07:09,811
This is nice, right here.

2517
02:07:09,894 --> 02:07:11,271
It's the house that Ray built.

2518
02:07:11,354 --> 02:07:12,397
Yes, it is.

2519
02:07:12,689 --> 02:07:14,399
♪ Born to lose ♪

2520
02:07:16,067 --> 02:07:19,738
♪ I've lived my life in vain ♪

2521
02:07:24,451 --> 02:07:26,244
Ray Junior, slow down!

2522
02:07:26,327 --> 02:07:28,204
This ain't no baseball diamond!

2523
02:07:30,665 --> 02:07:32,333
Charles residence.

2524
02:07:33,001 --> 02:07:34,627
Mr. Charles?

2525
02:07:34,836 --> 02:07:37,338
Hey, girl,
Bring that boy over here!

2526
02:07:37,422 --> 02:07:39,549
I got a hot dog with his 
name on it! Come on, now.

2527
02:07:39,632 --> 02:07:40,800
Hello.

2528
02:07:41,259 --> 02:07:43,386
Uh, yes, I know who you are.

2529
02:07:44,721 --> 02:07:46,890
What? Oh, God, no.

2530
02:07:47,432 --> 02:07:48,391
Ray.

2531
02:07:48,433 --> 02:07:51,936
Yes, I'll get on a plane and 
I'll be there as soon as I can.

2532
02:07:52,020 --> 02:07:53,355
What happened?

2533
02:07:55,482 --> 02:07:56,816
Margie's dead.

2534
02:07:57,192 --> 02:07:58,860
Oh, God! H-How?

2535
02:08:00,612 --> 02:08:02,113
She overdosed.

2536
02:08:05,492 --> 02:08:07,285
I didn't start her, Bea.

2537
02:08:08,453 --> 02:08:09,913
I didn't let her do dope around me.

2538
02:08:09,996 --> 02:08:11,956
I ... I just wouldn't
let that happen.

2539
02:08:12,040 --> 02:08:15,293
Yes, I'm sure, Ray.
I'm sure you set a fine example.

2540
02:08:19,464 --> 02:08:21,216
What about her baby?

2541
02:08:25,678 --> 02:08:26,971
You knew?

2542
02:08:27,681 --> 02:08:29,724
His name is Charles Wayne.

2543
02:08:30,100 --> 02:08:33,937
He was born October 1, in 
New York City. He's 3 years old.

2544
02:08:34,896 --> 02:08:36,398
The baby's fine.

2545
02:08:37,315 --> 02:08:39,109
He's at her sister's.

2546
02:08:40,860 --> 02:08:42,821
All right. I'll start sending 
them some money.

2547
02:08:42,904 --> 02:08:45,990
You don't have to.
I send them money every month.

2548
02:09:10,849 --> 02:09:12,475
In five minutes,
Mr. Charles will be here,

2549
02:09:12,517 --> 02:09:14,019
and he'll be ready to go.

2550
02:09:14,060 --> 02:09:15,645
Now the charts
Jeff is handing out ...

2551
02:09:15,687 --> 02:09:18,523
should be turned in
at the conclusion of ...

2552
02:09:18,940 --> 02:09:21,192
You're late, that's a $50 fine.

2553
02:09:21,735 --> 02:09:23,194
I ain't late.

2554
02:09:23,236 --> 02:09:25,321
I give them
a 10-minute grace period, Joe.

2555
02:09:25,405 --> 02:09:28,700
Five minutes after two. 
He's late. He'll be charged $50.

2556
02:09:28,783 --> 02:09:31,286
What? You know what?
Where's Ray?

2557
02:09:31,369 --> 02:09:33,705
You don't have to talk to Ray,
you're talking to me.

2558
02:09:33,788 --> 02:09:38,001
I'll talk to whoever I damn well 
please, and it sure as hell ain't you.

2559
02:09:38,043 --> 02:09:39,377
Jive jerk.

2560
02:09:44,132 --> 02:09:45,300
Hey, Ray,

2561
02:09:45,383 --> 02:09:49,512
this fool Joe Adams is trying 
to fine me for being late.

2562
02:09:49,804 --> 02:09:51,264
What time did you get here?

2563
02:09:51,348 --> 02:09:55,352
What? Just now.
The band's still setting up.

2564
02:09:55,935 --> 02:09:57,562
- Jeff don't ...
- Look, I'm not Jeff.

2565
02:09:57,645 --> 02:09:59,397
That's a fact, Jack!

2566
02:10:00,565 --> 02:10:03,234
Ray, you said the band was my thing.

2567
02:10:03,318 --> 02:10:04,778
It is.

2568
02:10:04,861 --> 02:10:07,530
Then, Fathead,
you go on back to rehearsal.

2569
02:10:08,573 --> 02:10:09,908
Ray.

2570
02:10:10,367 --> 02:10:12,786
Ray, you know how it is,
you've been there.

2571
02:10:13,328 --> 02:10:15,663
Fathead, go on now.
Let me handle this.

2572
02:10:15,747 --> 02:10:17,457
Fathead, go on now.

2573
02:10:20,919 --> 02:10:23,004
You want to tell me what the hell
is going on, Ray?

2574
02:10:23,088 --> 02:10:25,090
I'm not doing anything
I haven't been asked to.

2575
02:10:25,173 --> 02:10:26,716
Ray's running a business.

2576
02:10:26,800 --> 02:10:29,844
He shouldn't have to waste time
hearing why people were late.

2577
02:10:29,928 --> 02:10:31,721
I'm not talking to you, Joe.

2578
02:10:31,763 --> 02:10:33,515
I'm talking to Ray.

2579
02:10:38,478 --> 02:10:41,439
Ray, now I know you think
I'm soft on the band,

2580
02:10:41,481 --> 02:10:43,858
but those cats would do
whatever I ask.

2581
02:10:43,942 --> 02:10:46,611
But If you come in here with this, 
uh, "running a business" crap,

2582
02:10:46,653 --> 02:10:48,905
you're gonna lose some good people.
I'm telling you, Ray.

2583
02:10:48,947 --> 02:10:51,366
There are musicians waiting in 
line to play with Ray Charles.

2584
02:10:51,449 --> 02:10:54,285
Not for long,
once they get a taste of you.

2585
02:10:54,953 --> 02:10:57,163
Ray, you're the leader, man.
Be one! Come on, now.

2586
02:10:57,247 --> 02:10:59,249
You now what Jeff, I mean
things have changed.

2587
02:10:59,290 --> 02:11:02,377
It ain't like the days when it was 
seven of us on the Chitlin' Circuit.

2588
02:11:02,460 --> 02:11:05,922
I mean, if you weren't busy building 
a bowling alley, you'd seen that.

2589
02:11:06,297 --> 02:11:08,133
So you know about that, huh?

2590
02:11:08,591 --> 02:11:10,510
I know about everything.

2591
02:11:11,136 --> 02:11:13,096
I'm just trying to figure out
how you did it.

2592
02:11:13,179 --> 02:11:14,806
You think
I'm stealing from you, Ray?

2593
02:11:14,889 --> 02:11:18,143
If the Shaw Agency is gonna give you 
a cut of the 10% I'm given them.

2594
02:11:18,226 --> 02:11:21,187
I might as well keep the 
goddamn money in my pocket.

2595
02:11:21,479 --> 02:11:23,773
Leave us alone. We need to talk.

2596
02:11:24,858 --> 02:11:25,942
Ray.

2597
02:11:26,359 --> 02:11:28,403
You can step outside, Joe.

2598
02:11:30,238 --> 02:11:32,032
I'll be in my office.

2599
02:11:37,495 --> 02:11:41,374
Ray, now I know that jealous bastard
planted that lie in your head.

2600
02:11:42,500 --> 02:11:45,003
But I have never stolen
from you, Ray, and I never will.

2601
02:11:45,045 --> 02:11:48,882
I got a small business loan, and, yeah, 
Milt Shaw was giving me a little extra,

2602
02:11:48,965 --> 02:11:50,592
but I'm not a thief, Ray.

2603
02:11:50,675 --> 02:11:52,010
Then what about that, Jeff, huh?

2604
02:11:52,052 --> 02:11:56,139
A promoter swearing you did side deals 
with him so you could split my overages!

2605
02:11:56,222 --> 02:11:58,099
How could you do that to me?

2606
02:11:58,183 --> 02:12:00,268
We've been through so much,
we be so like brothers.

2607
02:12:00,352 --> 02:12:02,062
You know what, Ray?

2608
02:12:03,146 --> 02:12:06,149
If we were like brothers,

2609
02:12:06,483 --> 02:12:08,902
why are you paying Joe
more than you're paying me?

2610
02:12:08,985 --> 02:12:11,363
Damn all that!
You broke my heart, man.

2611
02:12:11,404 --> 02:12:15,742
Well, you know what, Ray? You broke 
mine a long goddamn time ago!

2612
02:12:16,576 --> 02:12:18,536
Well, then there it is.

2613
02:12:25,168 --> 02:12:26,795
You know something, Ray?

2614
02:12:26,878 --> 02:12:28,671
You're going to get yours one day.

2615
02:12:28,713 --> 02:12:32,550
And I pray to God that he has mercy 
on your soul, you son of a bitch!

2616
02:12:40,308 --> 02:12:42,352
Everything all right, Ray?

2617
02:12:43,561 --> 02:12:45,897
How the hell do you think it is?

2618
02:12:56,574 --> 02:12:59,911
Go tell him. Go tell him!
Go, go tell him.

2619
02:13:01,496 --> 02:13:02,872
Hey, Dad. Hi, there.

2620
02:13:02,914 --> 02:13:04,958
I made the all-star team!
The game's on Thursday.

2621
02:13:05,041 --> 02:13:06,084
Oh, that's great.

2622
02:13:06,167 --> 02:13:08,920
Oh, damn! I'm not gonna be in town.
I'm gotta go on tour.

2623
02:13:08,962 --> 02:13:11,548
How about I buy you guys
new uniforms, huh?

2624
02:13:11,631 --> 02:13:13,675
Tell the coach I don't care
how much they cost.

2625
02:13:13,758 --> 02:13:14,676
Okay.

2626
02:13:14,759 --> 02:13:17,303
All right, son, you want to take
your dad's briefcase inside.

2627
02:13:17,387 --> 02:13:20,015
The plane to Montreal leaves at 11:00.
I'll pick you up at 8:30.

2628
02:13:20,098 --> 02:13:21,057
All right.

2629
02:13:21,599 --> 02:13:23,560
Did you hear what
Ray Junior said to you?

2630
02:13:23,601 --> 02:13:24,561
Yeah.

2631
02:13:24,602 --> 02:13:26,938
Do you know how much making the 
all-star team means to him?

2632
02:13:27,022 --> 02:13:29,482
I know. I got things on my mind.
We had to fire Jeff.

2633
02:13:29,566 --> 02:13:30,567
What?

2634
02:13:30,608 --> 02:13:31,651
He was stealing.

2635
02:13:31,735 --> 02:13:32,819
- Jeff?
- Hmm.

2636
02:13:32,902 --> 02:13:34,195
I don't believe it.

2637
02:13:34,279 --> 02:13:36,239
Yeah, well, 
we're better without him.

2638
02:13:36,364 --> 02:13:38,825
♪ My mother told me ♪

2639
02:13:43,621 --> 02:13:46,249
♪ 'Fore she passed away ♪

2640
02:13:47,792 --> 02:13:51,463
♪ Said son when I'm gone ♪

2641
02:13:51,796 --> 02:13:53,757
♪ Don't forget to pray ♪

2642
02:13:53,798 --> 02:13:56,134
♪ 'Cause there'll be hard times ♪

2643
02:13:58,678 --> 02:14:01,264
♪ Hard times ♪

2644
02:14:01,306 --> 02:14:04,225
♪ Oh, yeah, yeah ♪

2645
02:14:04,309 --> 02:14:07,937
♪ Who knows better than I ♪

2646
02:14:37,258 --> 02:14:38,676
Excuse me! Get 'em out!

2647
02:14:39,135 --> 02:14:40,804
U.S. Customs!

2648
02:14:40,887 --> 02:14:43,181
We're goanna need to see some 
identification, please.

2649
02:14:43,264 --> 02:14:45,016
You just arrived from Montreal?

2650
02:14:45,058 --> 02:14:46,476
Yes. Is there a problem?

2651
02:14:46,518 --> 02:14:48,853
We were alerted there might 
be drugs on this plane.

2652
02:14:48,937 --> 02:14:51,314
What? That's outrageous!
I'm going to call our lawyer.

2653
02:14:51,356 --> 02:14:53,608
No lawyers
at international checkpoints.

2654
02:14:53,692 --> 02:14:56,194
Now, we're going to have to 
search everyone on this plane.

2655
02:14:56,277 --> 02:14:59,030
Mr. Charles, if you don't mind
we'd like to start with you.

2656
02:14:59,072 --> 02:15:00,949
I'd like to see your overcoat.

2657
02:15:01,032 --> 02:15:02,242
I don't mind.

2658
02:15:02,325 --> 02:15:03,702
Don't say anything, Ray.

2659
02:15:04,369 --> 02:15:05,412
What's this?

2660
02:15:07,372 --> 02:15:09,749
Ray, this isn't some judge
in Indiana.

2661
02:15:09,833 --> 02:15:11,876
It's federal. 
They can charge you with smuggling ...

2662
02:15:11,960 --> 02:15:13,670
which can mean real prison time.

2663
02:15:14,963 --> 02:15:17,966
Our lawyers will do
what they can, but ...

2664
02:15:37,736 --> 02:15:39,070
Hello.

2665
02:15:41,197 --> 02:15:43,074
You can't hide out
in here forever, Ray.

2666
02:15:43,116 --> 02:15:44,951
Look, it's my house.
I'm not in prison yet.

2667
02:15:45,035 --> 02:15:46,077
No, it's my house.

2668
02:15:46,161 --> 02:15:49,039
You ain't been here more than 
six days since we moved in.

2669
02:15:49,080 --> 02:15:51,166
No, Ray, no! 
A needle ain't gonna solve this!

2670
02:15:51,249 --> 02:15:52,208
Get out of the way. Move!

2671
02:15:52,250 --> 02:15:54,085
Only thing
that can help you is God, Ray.

2672
02:15:54,169 --> 02:15:56,880
Don't think of God? Do you have any 
idea how it feels to go blind ...

2673
02:15:56,921 --> 02:15:58,381
and still be afraid of the dark?

2674
02:15:58,423 --> 02:16:01,593
And every day, you stand pray for just 
a little light, and you get nothing.

2675
02:16:01,676 --> 02:16:03,511
'Cause God don't listen
to people like me.

2676
02:16:03,595 --> 02:16:04,637
Stop talking like that.

2677
02:16:04,721 --> 02:16:07,599
As far as I'm concerned, me and 
God is even and I do what I please.

2678
02:16:07,682 --> 02:16:09,726
If goddamn it, if I want 
to shoot up, I shoot up.

2679
02:16:09,809 --> 02:16:12,520
Then go ahead!
But you walk out that door ...

2680
02:16:12,604 --> 02:16:14,939
and I'm doing something I should 
have done a long time ago.

2681
02:16:15,023 --> 02:16:16,775
I'm taking my boys and I'll leave.

2682
02:16:16,816 --> 02:16:18,860
You're not going away.
You ... you have no place to go.

2683
02:16:18,943 --> 02:16:20,445
- No place?
- No.

2684
02:16:20,528 --> 02:16:22,614
You think I'm scared of losing this?

2685
02:16:22,697 --> 02:16:25,617
Ray, the only thing I was
ever scared of losing was you.

2686
02:16:25,700 --> 02:16:28,828
Because where was I ever gonna 
find another Ray Robinson?

2687
02:16:30,330 --> 02:16:32,916
So I put up with
some terrible stuff.

2688
02:16:33,124 --> 02:16:34,959
Maybe that makes me part to blame.

2689
02:16:35,043 --> 02:16:36,378
But I ain't scared no more.

2690
02:16:36,461 --> 02:16:39,130
You know I love you and those 
boys more than anything.

2691
02:16:39,214 --> 02:16:41,633
That is a damn lie
and you know it!

2692
02:16:43,176 --> 02:16:44,844
You ever look at this?

2693
02:16:45,095 --> 02:16:47,347
Really look at it, Ray!

2694
02:16:47,681 --> 02:16:50,767
Ray Charles Junior's
"Most Valuable Player."

2695
02:16:52,185 --> 02:16:54,354
He was so proud this day,

2696
02:16:55,438 --> 02:16:59,317
until you came home too loaded
to go to his banquet.

2697
02:16:59,359 --> 02:17:02,654
No! No! There is something you 
love more than me and them boys,

2698
02:17:02,696 --> 02:17:05,365
more than all the women you 
ever slept with on the road,

2699
02:17:05,448 --> 02:17:07,075
more than all
the dope you ever took.

2700
02:17:07,158 --> 02:17:09,494
- What are you talking about?
- Your music.

2701
02:17:11,371 --> 02:17:13,707
And if you don't stop
using that needle,

2702
02:17:13,832 --> 02:17:16,960
they're gonna take away your 
music and put you in jail.

2703
02:17:20,839 --> 02:17:23,174
Is that poison
worth losing everything?

2704
02:18:05,300 --> 02:18:06,968
Mr. Charles?

2705
02:18:19,356 --> 02:18:20,857
Mr. Charles.

2706
02:18:21,524 --> 02:18:23,318
You don't have to go through this.

2707
02:18:24,194 --> 02:18:28,031
We have a substitute that can 
help wean you off heroin.

2708
02:18:28,365 --> 02:18:32,577
I have to do it on my own.
I can do it. I can do it.

2709
02:18:33,286 --> 02:18:34,746
Ah. Don't touch me.

2710
02:18:38,083 --> 02:18:39,417
All right.

2711
02:18:39,918 --> 02:18:41,628
We'll do it your way.

2712
02:18:52,722 --> 02:18:54,057
Doctor?

2713
02:18:54,307 --> 02:18:57,352
Mr. Charles. Mr. Charles,
I'm coming.

2714
02:18:58,103 --> 02:18:59,813
He's got no fluids left.

2715
02:18:59,938 --> 02:19:01,690
Get an I.V. in him right away.

2716
02:19:02,107 --> 02:19:03,942
- I'll insert the needle.
- No needles.

2717
02:19:04,025 --> 02:19:05,944
Yes. It's very important.
You need this.

2718
02:19:06,027 --> 02:19:07,946
Runner, I've got a runner!

2719
02:19:08,613 --> 02:19:09,614
Whoa.

2720
02:19:11,199 --> 02:19:13,618
- Let me go. Let me go.
- Get him on the bed.

2721
02:19:14,202 --> 02:19:16,705
Put those restraints on him.

2722
02:19:17,163 --> 02:19:18,748
No needles.

2723
02:19:37,017 --> 02:19:38,476
No, no.

2724
02:19:39,477 --> 02:19:40,854
Oh.

2725
02:19:44,858 --> 02:19:47,193
George, I miss you.
I miss you, George.

2726
02:19:47,318 --> 02:19:49,654
I miss you.

2727
02:19:54,325 --> 02:19:55,660
Oh.

2728
02:20:08,840 --> 02:20:10,425
- Okay. 
- Uh-oh.

2729
02:20:10,508 --> 02:20:12,802
You might be in trouble
right there, Doc.

2730
02:20:21,770 --> 02:20:24,105
Hot damn,
you whupped my ass again!

2731
02:20:24,189 --> 02:20:26,941
I — I'll tell you what, I won't 
lose again the same way twice.

2732
02:20:27,025 --> 02:20:30,487
I spoke with the judge in Boston,
and he'll agree to probation.

2733
02:20:30,779 --> 02:20:33,031
He was impressed with
your attorney's arguments,

2734
02:20:33,114 --> 02:20:35,158
and he believes
you deserve one more chance.

2735
02:20:35,241 --> 02:20:36,659
Oh, that's great.

2736
02:20:36,701 --> 02:20:38,703
But you must complete 
